  "prompt": "What is a good amount of money yearly to live more than comfortably in the USA?",
  "response": "The amount of money needed to live more than comfortably in the USA can vary significantly based on factors like location, lifestyle, family size, and personal preferences. However, some general estimates can provide a rough idea. \n\nIn expensive cities such as San Francisco, New York, or Los Angeles, a household income of around $150,000 to $200,000 or more could be considered more than comfortable, allowing for a higher standard of living, including a spacious home, frequent dining out, travel, and savings for retirement. \n\nIn less expensive regions, such as the Midwest or parts of the South, a household income of $80,000 to $120,000 might offer a similar level of comfort, depending on the specific area and lifestyle choices.\n\nThese figures can vary greatly based on individual circumstances, so it's important to consider personal financial goals and priorities along with the local cost of living when determining what constitutes a \"more than comfortable\" income.",
